comments.body: Shouldn't this be `" are "`? Could you double-check?

For this case, no. Because the string generated by "KernelsRegisteredForOp" has a preceeding space.
With `` are `` you will have a string like this:  
```
Available kernels for Cast are  device='CPU
```
Note there are 2 spaces between "are" and "device".
Either one is fine with me though...
